  "text": "The GCC ICE with 'verify_gimple failed' traces through the following files and functions in the gcc--96dfb333 repository:\n\n1. **gcc/tree-cfg.cc** — This is the primary file implementing GIMPLE verification. It contains:\n   - `verify_gimple_in_seq` (line 5244): The top-level function that verifies GIMPLE statements in a sequence; if verification fails and ice=true, it calls `internal_error(\"%<verify_gimple%> failed\")`.\n   - `verify_gimple_stmt` (line 5034): Dispatches to per-statement verifiers (verify_gimple_assign, verify_gimple_call, etc.) to check individual GIMPLE statements.\n   - `verify_gimple_in_cfg` (line 5443): Verifies GIMPLE in a CFG context; also triggers `internal_error(\"verify_gimple failed\")` on failure.\n   - Many helper functions: `verify_gimple_assign`, `verify_gimple_call`, `verify_gimple_return`, `verify_gimple_cond`, `verify_gimple_goto`, `verify_gimple_switch`, `verify_gimple_debug`, `verify_gimple_label`, `verify_gimple_phi`, `verify_gimple_in_seq_2`, etc.\n\n2. **gcc/diagnostic-global-context.cc** — Defines the `internal_error` function (line 776) that is called when verification fails, triggering the ICE report.\n\n3. **gcc/passes.def** — The pass pipeline definition file. GIMPLE verification is not listed as a dedicated named pass here; instead, it is invoked as part of `TODO_verify_il` after each pass.\n\n4. **gcc/passes.cc** — The pass manager that schedules verification. At line 2702, `execute_todo` is called with `TODO_verify_il` after every optimization pass. At lines 2093-2102, `TODO_verify_il` triggers `verify_gimple_in_cfg` (when CFG exists) or `verify_gimple_in_seq` (otherwise). The `TODO_verify_il` flag (defined at line 71) is the mechanism by which GIMPLE verification is scheduled in the pass pipeline."
}

